<TITLE> Garment businessman shot dead </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 15 (bdnews24.com)  A readymade garment industry businessman was shot dead on Monday morning at the city's Kakrail crossing, a police official said. The victim, Abdus Salam Babu was the director of Yonk Group located at Purana Paltan. The incident occurred around 7:30am while Salam was driving to his workplace after dropping his child to school, sub-inspector of Paltan Police Station Gazi Fazlu told bdnews24.com. As he was about to reach Kakrail crossing three unknown people shot him thrice. Salam died on the way to Dhaka Medical College Hospital, the police official said. The police are trying to find out the reason behind the killing, Fazlu said. No case has been filed yet. bdne
